CasePhase ID, unique ID referencing to V_CasePhase usedto get information about the phase of this case. (e.g. periop,preop, intraop, postop). Loaded from the CaseMain.Case-ClassFRID and can be joined to CaseClass.FirstRevID.
CaseType ID, unique ID referencing to V_CaseType. Usedto get the type of this case (e.g. elective, emergency).Loaded from the CaseMain.CaseTypeFRID and can bejoined to CaseType.FirstRevID.

ASA ID, unique ID referencing to V_ASAClass, Used to getthe ASA class of this case. Loaded from the variable Map-Code (e.g. ASA in the global configuration) and can bejoined to ValueChoice.FirstRevID. The variable MapCode isconfigurable.

AneTechnique ID, unique ID referencing to V_AnesthesiaT-echnique, Used to get the primary anesthesia technique ofthis case. Loaded from the variable Primary anesthesia tech-nique and can be joined to ValueChoice.FirstRevID.

SurgicalService ID, unique ID referencing to V_SurgicalSer-vice, Used to get the surgical service of this case. Loadedfrom the CaseMain.ServiceFRID and can be joined to Ser-vice.FirstRevID.Column Name                 Data Type    Description
Diagnosis ID, unique ID referencing to V_ProcDiagList (Pri-mary Diagnose), Used to get the primary diagnosis of thiscase. Loaded from the PatientHealthProblem.Diagnosis-CodedItemFRID.
Diagnose ID, unique ID referencing to V_ProcDiagList (Pri-mary Procedure), Used to get the primary procedure of thiscase. Loaded from the PatientCode.CodedItemFRID.

Location ID, unique ID referencing to V_Location (locationsfor patient), Used to get the room of this case (e.g. operatingroom 1). Loaded from the PatientLocation.RoomFRID com-bined with PatientLocation.DepartmentFRID. Can only bejoined to the base tables by using the V_Loca-tion.Loc_RoomID=Room.FirstRevID and V_Loca-tion.Loc_DepartmentID=Department.FirstRevID.

Patient case age ID, unique ID referencing to V_PatientCa-seAge, Used to get patient case age of the case for group-ing, sorting, etc. Precalculated out of the patient's birthdayand case start time, using different granularities dependingon the age. For more details about these granularities, checksection “V_PatientCaseAge”.

Primary Anesthesiologist ID, unique ID referencing toV_Staff, Used to get the last primary anesthesiologist of thiscase. Loaded from the CasePersonnel.FirstRevID and canbe joined to StaffMember.FirstRevID. If more primary or non-primary staff is needed the fact table F_StaffUsage needs tobe joined by using the CasD_ID.

Primary Surgeon, unique ID referencing to V_Staff, Used toget the last primary surgeon of this case. Loaded from theCasePersonnel.FirstRevID and can be joined to StaffMem-ber.FirstRevID. If more primary or non-primary staff isneeded the fact table F_StaffUsage needs to be joined byusing the CasD_ID.

Primary Nurse, unique ID referencing to V_Staff, Used to getthe last primary nurse of this case. Loaded from theCasePersonnel.FirstRevID and can be joined to StaffMem-ber.FirstRevID. If more primary or non-primary staff isneeded the fact table F_StaffUsage needs to be joined byusing the CasD_ID.
